description:
Join us for a guided walk of our exhibition We don’t end at our edges. It is an immersive exhibition featuring artworks by Bengaluru-based artist, writer and educator Ravikumar Kashi. He uses paper to ‘paint’ letters from the Kannada alphabet, transforming language itself into a metaphor for the permeability of human connection, suggesting that while physical forms may fade, the bonds we share as individuals and as a community remain.

Join this guided walk for a deeper understanding of the exhibition.

&nbsp;
